Instagram's approach to quality control through dogfooding is indeed innovative and insightful. By leveraging the experience of their own employees as users, they create a feedback loop that is both rapid and direct, ensuring that the product remains user-centric and robust.

This method, combined with the hiring of world-class engineers who are genuinely passionate about quality, elevates the entire engineering process. While having a high automated test coverage is certainly valuable, it often doesn't capture the nuances of real user experience.

